The paper deals with the problem of finding smooth orthogonal layouts of planar graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of edge complexity is related to the representation of graphs as data structures, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of graph properties such as planarity and biconnectivity, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of smooth orthogonal layouts, which is a topic in computational complexity and algorithmic lower bounds (cs.SI).
